# INSTALLATION

## Install node in ubuntu

The NodeSource repository provides the latest Node.js packages for Ubuntu. This NodeSource repository for Node.js 18 LTS can be added to the system using the command:

curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -

Once the repository has been added, install Node.js 18 LTS on Ubuntu 22.04|20.04|18.04 using the command:

sudo apt-get install nodejs

Once complete, verify the installed version.

$ node -v
v18.0.0

